                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120115-114-victim1081 t18120115-114-viclabel680"></join>; I carry on the business of a <rs id="t18120115-114-viclabel681" type="occupation">rope and twine manufacturer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120115-114-victim1081 t18120115-114-viclabel681"></join>.</p>
               <p>Q. How long has your husband been dead - A. Nine years, and the prisoner has been my servant five years; I entrusted him to take out goods and receive the money.</p>
               <p>Q. Did the prisoner give you any account of money received on the 12th of December - A. He did not. When I found out that he had been embezzling money of Boyer and Company; I went round to my customers and found that he had received the money of Stock and Company and gave a receipt in my name; he has received forty-three pounds at different times.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120115-114-person1083">
                  FORD 
                  WILSON
               <interp inst="t18120115-114-person1083" type="surname" value="WILSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120115-114-person1083" type="given" value="FORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120115-114-person1083" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a servant to Stock, Cooper, and Company. On the 12th of December the prisoner brought a dozen skeins of cord, it came to one pound, I paid him, he gave me this receipt.</p>
               <p>"Bought of Mrs. Allanson a dozen skeins of cord, one pound. Received, 
               <persName id="t18120115-114-person1084">
                  William 
                  Budd
               <interp inst="t18120115-114-person1084" type="surname" value="Budd"></interp>
